nhc_headline: ...NARDA CONTINUES WEAKENING OVER OPEN WATERS... ...LIKELY TO BECOME POST-TROPICAL LATER TODAY OR EARLY MONDAY...
summary: ...NARDA CONTINUES WEAKENING OVER OPEN WATERS... ...LIKELY TO BECOME POST-TROPICAL LATER TODAY OR EARLY MONDAY... As of 8:00 AM PDT Sun Sep 28 the center of Narda was located near 19.7, -125.5 with movement N at 6 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1000 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 50 mph.
